## Gotchas
WRONG: validating JWT by decoding only (jwt.decode)
RIGHT: verify signature against JWKS endpoint
WHY: jwt.decode does not verify the signature. Anyone can forge a token. Always verify.

WRONG: hardcoding realm URL
RIGHT: use KEYCLOAK_URL and KEYCLOAK_REALM env vars
WHY: Realm URL differs per environment. Hardcoding breaks staging/production.

[Add more WRONG/RIGHT/WHY blocks as you discover them.]

